_json.gridTitle: One cool cottage: An interior designer bigs up a small space
_json.description: Three small rooms at the back of the house were knocked into one large open-plan kitchen-diner with french doors leading out to the garden. The tongue-and-groove panelling is painted in Little Greene’s Shirting (littlegreene.com), while the fireplace is in Farrow & Ball’s Down Pipe (farrow-ball.com). For a similar table try The French House (thefrenchhouse.co.uk). Simon found the vintage Tolix chairs on Ebay; they are available new from Made In Design (madeindesign.co.uk). Urban Cottage Indu...
